It depends on situation.

If the record has been deleted by something like `$model-&gt;delete()` and you still have the instance `$model` than you can do `$model-&gt;save()` to restore it, because even after deletion the instance of $model still have the values of attributes before deletion.

If you&#39;ve already lost the instance of `$model` or if you never had it in first place (for example because the delete has been done using something like `Model::deleteAll($condition)` then you can&#39;t recover it using this approach. 

This also won&#39;t recover any related records that might be removed by `ON DELETE CASCADE`.

If you need to recover record in different request than the one that deleted it. You can store `$model` in session then get it from there and do `$model-&gt;save()`
For example like this:
```
public function actionDelete()
{
    $model = Author::findOne(2);
    $model-&gt;delete();

    Yii::$app-&gt;session-&gt;set(&#39;model&#39;, $model);
}

public function actionRestore()
{
    if (Yii::$app-&gt;session-&gt;has(&#39;model&#39;)) {
        $model = Yii::$app-&gt;session-&gt;get(&#39;model&#39;);
        $model-&gt;save();
    }
}
```

